<!-- ==================== SECTION 1 ==================== -->
<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>

<p>This document compares two Microsoft Power Platform options for migrating the <b>Advisory AI Ideas</b> React/TypeScript application: <b>Power Apps (Canvas App)</b> and <b>Power Pages</b>. Each platform has different strengths depending on your priorities around design fidelity, development speed, governance, and user experience.</p>

<table>
<tr>
    <th style="width:25%;">Criteria</th>
    <th style="width:37%;">Power Apps (Canvas App)</th>
    <th style="width:38%;">Power Pages</th>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Best for</b></td>
    <td>Internal teams, fast low-code delivery, tight Microsoft 365 integration</td>
    <td>Pixel-perfect design, external-facing portals, full HTML/CSS/JS control</td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Estimated timeline</b></td>
    <td>3 &ndash; 5 days (AI-assisted)</td>
    <td>4 &ndash; 7 days (AI-assisted)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Design fidelity</b></td>
    <td>~70&ndash;80% match to current UI</td>
    <td>~95&ndash;100% match to current UI</td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Licensing cost</b></td>
    <td>Included with most Microsoft 365 E3/E5 plans</td>
    <td>Separate Power Pages license required</td>
</tr>
</table>

<div class="callout">
<b>Bottom line:</b> Choose <b>Power Apps</b> if the audience is internal KPMG staff and speed matters most. Choose <b>Power Pages</b> if keeping the exact current interface design is the top priority or if external users will access the platform.
</div>

