<h2>3. Platform Overviews</h2>

<h3>3.1 Power Apps (Canvas App)</h3>
<p>A <b>low-code</b> app builder within Microsoft Power Platform. You design screens by dragging and arranging controls on a canvas, and write logic in <b>Power Fx</b> (a formula language similar to Excel). Apps run inside the Power Apps player on web, mobile, and Teams.</p>
<ul>
    <li>Drag-and-drop screen builder with 200+ built-in controls</li>
    <li>Native Dataverse connector &mdash; no API coding needed</li>
    <li>Power Fx formulas replace TypeScript business logic</li>
    <li>Copilot in Power Apps can generate screens from natural-language prompts</li>
    <li>Built-in user authentication via Azure AD</li>
</ul>

<h3>3.2 Power Pages</h3>
<p>A <b>low-code website platform</b> (formerly Power Apps Portals) for building data-driven web sites connected to Dataverse. You get a visual Design Studio <i>plus</i> full access to inject custom <b>HTML, CSS, and JavaScript</b>, so you can replicate the existing React interface nearly pixel-for-pixel.</p>
<ul>
    <li>Full HTML/CSS/JS editing within the portal framework</li>
    <li>Liquid templates for server-side data binding to Dataverse</li>
    <li>Web API for client-side CRUD against Dataverse tables</li>
    <li>Built-in authentication for both internal (Azure AD) and external users</li>
    <li>Copilot in Power Pages can generate page layouts and forms</li>
</ul>

