<h3>4.3 Business Logic Translation</h3>

<p>The application contains two critical calculation engines. Here is how each platform handles them:</p>

<h4>Weighted Value Score (from ideaService.ts)</h4>
<table>
<tr>
    <th style="width:15%;">Platform</th>
    <th>Implementation</th>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Power Apps</b></td>
    <td><code style="font-size:9pt;">Set(valueScore, ScoreMap(businessGrowth)*0.20 + ScoreMap(costEfficiency)*0.20 + ScoreMap(businessResilience)*0.30 + ScoreMap(businessAgility)*0.30)</code><br/>Uses Power Fx formula directly in the assessment form screen. ScoreMap is a Switch() that converts low/medium/high &rarr; 1/2/3.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Power Pages</b></td>
    <td>Option A: Reuse the exact TypeScript <code>calculateValueScore()</code> function in a <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> block on the page.<br/>Option B: Define as a Dataverse calculated column so scoring is server-side.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h4>Quadrant Determination (threshold = 2.0)</h4>
<table>
<tr>
    <th style="width:15%;">Platform</th>
    <th>Implementation</th>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Power Apps</b></td>
    <td><code style="font-size:9pt;">If(valueScore>=2 And feasScore>=2, "likely_wins", valueScore>=2 And feasScore&lt;2, "calculated_risks", valueScore&lt;2 And feasScore>=2, "marginal_gains", "avoid")</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td><b>Power Pages</b></td>
    <td>Reuse the existing <code>determineQuadrant()</code> JavaScript function as-is, or compute via Dataverse business rule.</td>
</tr>
</table>

