<h2>10. Recommendation</h2>

<div class="callout-green">

<h3>If the app is for internal KPMG users only &rarr; Power Apps (Canvas App)</h3>
<p>Power Apps delivers a functional app in 3&ndash;5 days with minimal coding. The design won't be pixel-perfect, but it will be close enough for internal use. You save on licensing costs, get native Teams integration, and benefit from the simplest maintenance model. The weighted scoring and approval workflows translate directly to Power Fx and Power Automate.</p>

<h3>If design fidelity or external access is required &rarr; Power Pages</h3>
<p>Power Pages lets you reuse the existing React CSS and JavaScript almost as-is, achieving near-identical design. It's the only option if external stakeholders or clients need access. Budget 4&ndash;7 days and the additional license cost. The trade-off is worthwhile when the visual experience and external reach are business-critical.</p>

<h3>Hybrid option: Start with Power Apps, extend with Power Pages later</h3>
<p>Since both platforms share the same Dataverse backend, you can launch quickly with a Canvas App for internal teams, then stand up a Power Pages portal on the same data for external-facing needs. This "start fast, extend later" approach minimizes upfront cost and timeline while keeping the door open for design-perfect external access.</p>

